               <floruit notBefore="1726" notAfter="1732">He was an important figure in the early 18th century Gondarine kingdom of Qwaraññā family. 
                  He played a major role in <persName ref="PRS2682BerhanM"/>'s maternal family's accession to power. 
                  In <date>1731</date>, he was promoted to 
                  <persName ref="PRS7585Niqolawo"><roleName type="title">daǧǧāzmāč</roleName>
                     Niqolāwos</persName>of <placeName ref="LOC5671Semen"/> and <placeName ref="LOC6198Wanata"/>.
                  In the following year, in <date>1731</date>,  
                  he became <persName ref="PRS7585Niqolawo"><roleName type="title">rās </roleName> 
                     Niqolāwos</persName>, and finally, in October <date>1732</date>
                  <persName ref="PRS7585Niqolawo"><roleName type="title">rās bitwaddad</roleName> Niqolāwos</persName>, a position that make him second in power to the regent queen. After his death, 
                  this position was overtaken by <persName ref="PRS2682BerhanM"/>'s brother, <persName ref="PRS9931WaldaLe"/>.
               </floruit>
               <death when="1732"/>
